# Build context excludes for both Dockerfiles. Without this file, the
# `lineage-service` build context exceeds 10 GB because `COPY . .` pulls in
# the Rust `target/` (~9 GB), Scala sbt caches, demo result fixtures, the
# `.git` history, etc. — leading to multi-minute build context transfers
# and frequent BuildKit "input/output error" crashes on disk-pressured
# Docker daemons.
#
# Each pattern is matched against the path *relative to the build context
# root* (the repo root). Subdirectory names like `target/` match anywhere.
#
# Keep this in sync with `.gitignore` (binary build artifacts only — source
# files that are committed should NOT be listed here).

# Version control history — never needed at build time.
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Rust build outputs — `open-lakehouse-table-service/Dockerfile` runs
# `cargo build --release` in a clean stage anyway, so any pre-built
# `target/` from the host is wasted.
target/
**/target/

# Scala / sbt build outputs from the Spark plugin.
spark-openlineage-plugin/target/
spark-openlineage-plugin/project/target/
spark-openlineage-plugin/project/project/
spark-openlineage-plugin/.bloop/
spark-openlineage-plugin/.metals/
spark-openlineage-plugin/.bsp/

# Demo result fixtures — committed for reference but not needed in image.
demo/results/

# Buf-generated proto export — recreated inside the Rust Dockerfile's
# proto stage. Keeping a stale host copy can mask wrong-version bugs.
open-lakehouse-table-service/proto-export/

# Editor / IDE state.
.idea/
.vscode/
.metals/
.bloop/
.bsp/
.cursor/
**/.DS_Store

# Local env files & secrets.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Test outputs / coverage.
*.coverprofile
coverage.*
*.out
*.test

# Local Spark/Derby state.
metastore_db/
derby.log

# Docker-specific.
.dockerignore
docker-compose*.yaml
docker-compose*.yml
Dockerfile*

# Project-internal docs that don't belong in any image.
AGENTS.md
README.md
*.md
